title: "Oracle Fusion Global Template Rollout – Singapore Deployment"
sub-title: "Key Considerations for Implementing a Global Template for Singapore-Based Finance & Operations Teams"

objList:
  - text: Singapore Financial Reporting & Regulatory Alignment
    icon: balance
    desc: Ensure the global template incorporates Singapore accounting, tax and regulatory needs.
    notes:
      - Align global Fusion design with Singapore Financial Reporting Standards (SFRS) where they differ from IFRS.
      - Support Singapore statutory reporting, XBRL filing formats and MAS (Monetary Authority of Singapore) guidelines.
      - Ensure GST (Goods & Services Tax) configuration aligns with IRAS requirements including reverse charge and exempt supplies.
      - Validate withholding tax rules for cross-border services, royalties and interest payments.

  - text: Local Operating Model & Singapore Team Structure
    icon: groups
    desc: Adapt the global process design to Singapore’s finance function and shared service participation.
    notes:
      - Identify whether Singapore acts as a regional APAC hub or a local functional team.
      - Clarify responsibilities for P2P, O2C, R2R between local teams, shared services and HQ.
      - Support Singapore’s typically lean finance teams with process automation and simplified workflows.
      - Prepare targeted change management for Singapore teams who value clarity, structure and efficiency.

  - text: Multi-Entity, Multi-Currency & Regional APAC Requirements
    icon: public
    desc: Ensure the design accommodates multi-currency operations and regional APAC regulatory diversity.
    notes:
      - Enable robust multi-currency processing including SGD, USD, EUR, CNY and other APAC currencies.
      - Align ledger and balancing segment design to accommodate Singapore entity structures.
      - Support regional intercompany transactions with consistent accounting rules and eliminations.
      - Address regional tax complexity where Singapore interacts with Hong Kong, Australia and other APAC markets.

  - text: GST Configuration & IRAS Compliance
    icon: receipt_long
    desc: Apply GST rules and reporting flows required by the Inland Revenue Authority of Singapore (IRAS).
    notes:
      - Configure GST codes for standard-rated, zero-rated, exempt and reverse charge transactions.
      - Support automatic GST reporting, adjustments and reconciliations within Fusion.
      - Ensure AP invoice workflows capture GST treatment accurately at line-level.
      - Validate GST reporting outputs for IRAS filing and audits.

  - text: Banking, Payments & Local Market Integrations
    icon: account_balance
    desc: Enable accurate and compliant integrations with Singapore’s banking landscape.
    notes:
      - Configure payables to support FAST, GIRO, MAS Electronic Payment System (MEPS) and SWIFT formats.
      - Integrate with major Singapore banks such as DBS, UOB, OCBC and Standard Chartered.
      - Support foreign currency bank accounts with auto-revaluation and translation rules.
      - Implement bank statement automation aligned to Singapore cash management practises.

  - text: Procurement & Supplier Management Localisation
    icon: shopping_cart
    desc: Tailor P2P processes to Singapore’s procurement policies and compliance standards.
    notes:
      - Capture supplier GST registration, IRAS validation and WHT applicability.
      - Configure approval routing based on Singapore cost centres, budgets and delegated authorities.
      - Support invoice matching practises common in APAC (3-way, 2-way, ERS).
      - Address local contract terms, freight handling, and cross-border services invoicing.

  - text: Financial Close, Reporting & Statutory Compliance
    icon: checklist
    desc: Align period close with Singapore statutory deadlines and reporting obligations.
    notes:
      - Singapore teams often close quickly; ensure global calendar supports local timelines.
      - Provide automated reconciliations through ARCS for cash, GST, payroll and intercompany.
      - Support SFRS statutory adjustments, audit adjustments and local financial statement generation.
      - Maintain drill-back capability for IRAS or auditor queries.

  - text: Data Migration & Singapore Cutover Considerations
    icon: sync_alt
    desc: Ensure clean migration of Singapore legacy data into the global template.
    notes:
      - Map legacy COA, customer, supplier and tax codes into the global structure.
      - Cleanse GST-related fields, especially historical tax treatment and exemption flags.
      - Avoid cutover during financial year-end (March or December depending on the company).
      - Validate migrated bank accounts, approval hierarchies and local integrations.

  - text: APAC Regional Integrations & Third-Party Platforms
    icon: cloud_sync
    desc: Integrate local and regional systems into the global template architecture.
    notes:
      - Connect to APAC payroll platforms (e.g., SAP SuccessFactors, Workday, ADP APAC).
      - Integrate with Singapore HR, expense or travel systems commonly used regionally.
      - Support MAS and IRAS reporting tools where required.
      - Ensure currency feeds, FX rate APIs and treasury systems reflect APAC FX volatility.

  - text: Working Practices, Training & Cultural Considerations
    icon: school
    desc: Deliver training and change management tailored to Singapore’s communication and work style.
    notes:
      - Provide structured, well-documented process guides for Singapore teams.
      - Use shorter, focused training sessions aligned to Singapore’s efficient working culture.
      - Deliver training in APAC time zones and include practical examples with GST and multi-currency impacts.
      - Emphasise standardisation benefits while addressing local compliance concerns.

  - text: Time Zone, Project Delivery & Hypercare Alignment
    icon: schedule
    desc: Align global project execution with Singapore’s business hours and APAC support needs.
    notes:
      - Establish a clear overlap window between Singapore and global design teams.
      - Schedule UAT cycles in Singapore time zones to ensure local participation.
      - Provide hypercare with APAC-hour coverage to address early issues quickly.
      - Adapt communication cadence to suit APAC availability and regional holidays.

  - text: Testing, Local Scenarios & Compliance Coverage
    icon: rule
    desc: Ensure test cycles reflect Singapore’s business flows and compliance activities.
    notes:
      - Include GST calculation, reverse charge, import GST and exempt supply scenarios in SIT and UAT.
      - Validate multi-currency revaluation, translation and FX accounting for SGD-ledger entities.
      - Test FAST/GIRO/payment file integrations with local banks.
      - Involve Singapore finance SMEs in end-to-end testing of procurement, AP, AR and close processes.

  - text: Future Scalability & APAC Expansion Readiness
    icon: auto_awesome
    desc: Prepare the global template for expansion across APAC leveraging Singapore’s strategic role.
    notes:
      - Ensure COA and ledger structures can scale for future APAC business growth.
      - Position Singapore as a potential regional finance or treasury hub.
      - Build flexibility for future GST rate changes or IRAS rule amendments.
      - Integrate AHCS, ARCS and reporting layers for a unified APAC finance platform.
